score.explanation: Your Wi-Fi network is performing well with strong signal quality, minimal interference, and sufficient bandwidth for your needs.
score.trend_summary: Since last scan: download worsened, upload improved, ping improved, networks decreased.

latest_report.diagnosis: Your network is experiencing random dropouts, which may be influenced by heavy congestion in both 2.4GHz and 5GHz bands. Strong interference from neighboring networks can impact performance.

performance.interpretation: The download speed is close to your subscribed plan, while upload speed is slightly below expected. Ping times are decent.

problems: Heavy congestion on the 2.4GHz band with multiple overlapping networks.
Multiple networks on the same 5GHz channel leading to potential interference.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 1 to reduce congestion (currently on heavily used channel 11).
Switch the 5GHz channel to 149 for less congestion (currently on crowded channel 36).
Consider relocating the router closer to the center of the home for better coverage.
Enable QoS to prioritize gaming traffic.
Ensure devices are connected to the 5GHz band where possible for better performance.
Reduce interference by moving away from windows and electronic devices.
